Coupon fraud happens when users exploit discount systems unfairly to get more benefits than intended.

Common real-world examples

Using the same coupon multiple times

Creating multiple fake accounts to reuse a first-time coupon

Applying coupons after expiry

Combining coupons in ways not allowed

Bots automatically applying coupons at scale

Impact on business:

Revenue loss

Skewed marketing analytics

Inventory and pricing issues

Increased operational cost
